=head1 OutputHandler class

This class handles all forms of output for the GridShib-CA.

=head2 Configuration Parameters

This class uses the following values from F<gridshib-ca.conf>:

=over 4

=item <Templates>Path</Templates>

Path to location where template files are stored.

=item <Templates>ErrorTempalte</Tempaltes>

Path to template file for error output.

=back

=head2 Methods

=over 4

=cut

package GridShibCA::OutputHandler;

use GridShibCA::Config;

=item new()

Create a new OutputHandler object.

B<Arguments:> None

B<Returns:> OutputHandler instance

=cut

sub new
{
    my $class = shift;
    my $self = {};
    my $self->{error} = undef;
    bless($self, $class);
    return $self;
}


=item outputHTML()

=cut

sub outputHTML
{
}


=item getError()

Return Error message associated with last error.

B<Arguments:> None

B<Returns:> String containing Error Message from last error. May be
undef if no error has occurred.

=cut

sub getError
{
    my $self = shift;
    return $self->{error};
}

=back

=cut

######################################################################

=head2 Internal methods

These internal methods not intended for external use.

=over 4

=item _error()

Handle a error message.

B<Arguments:> As to sprintf()

B<Returns:> Nothing

=cut

sub _error
{
    my $self = shift;
    my $format = shift;
    $self->{error} = sprintf($format, @_);
}

=back

=head2 Version

GridShib-CA version @PACKAGE_VERSION_STRING@ ($Id$)

=cut

